The article is a statement by the White House Press Secretary regarding a meeting held by the President in the Oval Office to discuss the situation in the Gulf of Mexico. The President was briefed by senior officials on ongoing search and rescue efforts, as well as efforts to mitigate and respond to the environmental impact of the incident. The President emphasized that this response is a top priority and requested that all necessary resources be devoted to the incident and its investigation. The National Response Team has been activated and coordination efforts have been established. The Department of the Interior, Minerals Management Service, and Coast Guard are working with responsible parties to secure pollution sources. The President expressed gratitude for the efforts of professionals working to save lives and protect the environment.